                            <comment id="62245" author="jhammond" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2013 11:42:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Both patches landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57879" author="jhammond" created="Wed, 8 May 2013 02:52:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please see &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/6285&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/6285&lt;/a&gt; for the ll_dir_getstripe()/lod_xattr_get()/fs root LOV EA fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57873" author="jhammond" created="Tue, 7 May 2013 23:44:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this may only apply to getting lov on the root. In lod_xattr_get() the lmm returned is in the host byte order. I&apos;ll submit a patch this evening.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57817" author="liwei" created="Tue, 7 May 2013 13:31:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It turned out the ll_dir_getstripe path needs fixing as well.  On an x86 client talking to a SPARC server, I got:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LustreError: 23875:0:(dir.c:871:ll_dir_getstripe()) unknown magic: D00BD10B&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
